             lipid-lowering medication, smoking, evidence of thyroid, liver, lung, heart or kidney
             disease, non-sedentary occupation, and VO2max levels above the considered average
             fitness according to age (Shvartz &amp; Reibold 1990), contraindications to increased
             levels of physical activity.
